## 4. Modules

### 4.1 Auth
- **Ref:** `Auth`
- **Backend:** `authController.js` — `POST /auth/login`, `GET /auth/me`
- **Frontend:** `LoginPage.jsx`, `AuthContext.jsx`
- **Mechanism:** JWT token in `localStorage`, Axios global `Authorization` header
- **Flow:** Login → JWT issued → `fetchMe()` on load → privileges resolved → `ProtectedRoute` guards modules
- **Password:** bcrypt-hashed in seeder, validated at login

### 4.2 AI Tool Maker
- **Ref:** `AI_Tool_Maker`
- **Backend:** `toolController.js` — CRUD (`getTools`, `getTool`, `createTool`, `updateTool`, `deleteTool`)
- **Frontend:** `ToolMaker.jsx` — form with fields: nombre, descripcion, logo (emoji), training_prompt, behavior_prompt, response_format, output_format, json_schema, ai_provider override
- **Business Rules:**
  - Tools have System Instruction split into Context (`training_prompt`) and Behavior (`behavior_prompt`)
  - Optional JSON Schema binding for structured output validation
  - Optional OutputFormat binding for HTML rendering templates
  - Optional per-tool AI Provider override (falls back to system default)

### 4.3 AI Tool Catalog
- **Ref:** `AI_Tool_Catalog`
- **Backend:** `toolController.js` — `getTools`
- **Frontend:** `Catalog.jsx` — card grid with search filter, tool count badge, launch/edit links
- **UX:** Cards show logo, name, description, response format badge, edit gear button, launch arrow

### 4.4 AI Tool Execution
- **Ref:** `AI_Tool_Execution`
- **Backend:** `toolController.js` — `POST /tools/:id/execute`
- **Frontend:** `ToolView.jsx` — execution hub with input form, file upload, result display
- **Execution Flow:**
  1. Client sends `{ requirementInstructions, file? }` via `multipart/form-data`
  2. Backend resolves AI provider: tool-specific override → system default (`is_default: true`)
  3. Builds prompt: `training_prompt + behavior_prompt + "#DATA#: " + requirementInstructions`
  4. If JSON response + JsonSchema: `cleanSchema()` removes unsupported Gemini keywords (`$ref`, `definitions`, `additionalProperties`, `default`, `enum` length validation)
  5. Routes to execution strategy:
     - **`google_native`** — Google Generative AI SDK (`generateContent`)
     - **`openai_compatible`** — Standard OpenAI chat completions API (OpenRouter, Groq, Together, Ollama, etc.)
  6. `sanitizeResponse()` strips markdown code fences (` ```json `, ` ``` `)
  7. If JSON format: parse → apply OutputFormat HTML template with `{{placeholder}}` replacement
  8. Return `{ success, data: { text, json?, html? } }`
- **Multimodal Support:** Images (PNG, JPEG, WebP, HEIC), PDF, text files, audio (MP3, WAV), video (MP4, AVI)
- **Supported MIME types:** `image/png`, `image/jpeg`, `image/webp`, `image/heic`, `image/heif`, `application/pdf`, `text/plain`, `text/javascript`, `text/python`, `text/csv`, `audio/mpeg`, `audio/wav`, `video/mp4`, `video/avi`

### 4.5 Config
- **Ref:** `Config`
- **Backend:** `configController.js` — `getConfigs`, `upsertConfig`
- **Frontend:** `Config.jsx` — system settings editor (key-value pairs, AI providers CRUD, user management)
- **Subsections in Config page:**
  - General config (key-value)
  - AI Providers management (full CRUD with masked API keys)
  - User management (CRUD with role assignment)
  - Privilege management (per-role per-module granular permissions)

### 4.6 AI Providers
- **Ref:** `AI_Providers`
- **Backend:** `aiProviderController.js` — CRUD + `setDefault`
- **Business Rules:**
  - API keys masked with `•` on read (show last 4 chars only via `maskKey()`)
  - Masked keys ignored on update (won't overwrite with dots)
  - Only one default provider at a time (atomic `setDefault` unsets all then sets one)
  - Cannot delete the current default provider
  - Two provider types: `google_native` (uses SDK), `openai_compatible` (uses REST API)
  - Extra headers support (JSON string) for provider-specific headers

### 4.7 JSON Schemas
- **Ref:** `Json_Schemas`
- **Backend:** `jsonSchemaController.js` — full CRUD
- **Frontend:** `JsonSchemaMaker.jsx` — schema editor with JSON validation
- **Purpose:** Reusable JSON Schema contracts for AI tool structured output validation

### 4.8 Outputs Maker
- **Ref:** `Outputs_Maker`
- **Backend:** `outputController.js` — CRUD for categories and formats
- **Frontend:** `OutputMaker.jsx` — HTML template editor with `{{placeholder}}` system
- **Structure:** OutputCategory → OutputFormat (tipo: reporte | accionable | generativo)
- **Template system:** HTML with `{{fieldName}}` placeholders replaced by parsed JSON output fields

### 4.9 Machines
- **Ref:** `Machines`
- **Backend:** `machineController.js` — full CRUD with graph atomics
- **Frontend:** `MachineCatalog.jsx` (card grid), `MachineEditor.jsx` (visual flow editor)
- **Concept:** Machines are visual DAG workflows that chain Tools and Engines into recursive execution flows
- **Graph persistence:** Full graph replacement on save (delete all → recreate nodes → recreate connections)
- **Editor UX:** Fullscreen dark pizarra (#0a0e1a), compact w-56 collapsible sidebar, React Flow canvas
  - Tool nodes: cyan accents with dark gradient cards
  - Engine nodes: violet accents with dark purple gradient cards
  - Edges: `smoothstep` with `ArrowClosed` markers in violet
  - Drag from sidebar → drop on canvas → connect handles → save
  - Delete nodes/edges with Backspace/Delete
  - MiniMap + Controls styled in dark theme

### 4.10 Engines
- **Ref:** (part of `Machines` module)
- **Backend:** `engineController.js` — read-only `getEngines`
- **Nature:** System-seeded, immutable base components for list processing in Machines
- **Types:**

| Engine | Slug | Tipo | Behavior |
|--------|------|------|----------|
| 🔄 List Iterator | `list-iterator` | `iterator` | Receives array, executes next connected Tool per item |
| 📦 List Collector | `list-collector` | `collector` | Aggregates individual Tool outputs into a single array |
| 🔀 Data Mapper | `data-mapper` | `mapper` | Transforms/maps fields between node inputs and outputs |

---

## 5. Security

### Authentication
- JWT-based, token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- `localStorage` persistence on frontend
- `authMiddleware` decodes JWT → loads User with Role → loads Privilegios → attaches `canRead`, `canWrite`, `canExec` to `req.user`

### Authorization — Privilege Engine
- **Granular:** per-module `read`, `write`, `exec` permissions
- **Wildcard:** `ref_modulo: '*'` grants access to all modules
- **Middleware:** `requirePrivilege(moduleName, action)` checks `req.user.can{Action}(module)`
- **Frontend mirror:** `AuthContext` exposes `canRead()`, `canWrite()`, `canExec()`, `isAdmin`
- **Route guard:** `<ProtectedRoute module="X">` blocks rendering if no read access

### Modules with privileges:
`Auth`, `AI_Tool_Maker`, `AI_Tool_Catalog`, `AI_Tool_Execution`, `Config`, `Outputs_Maker`, `Json_Schemas`, `AI_Providers`, `Machines`

### API Key Security
- Provider API keys masked on all GET responses (only last 4 chars visible)
- Masked values ignored on PUT/PATCH to prevent accidental overwrite

