## 11. Best Practices & Conventions

### Backend
- All IDs are UUID v4 (auto-generated by Sequelize)
- Consistent response format: `{ success: boolean, data?: any, message?: string }`
- Error handling: try/catch with `res.status(500).json({ success: false, message: error.message })`
- File uploads to `uploads/` directory (temporary, read and delete on use)
- DB sync: `sequelize.sync({ force: false })` — non-destructive by default
- DB pool: max 5, idle timeout 10s, acquire timeout 30s

### Frontend
- Functional components with hooks
- Context API for global state (auth only)
- Axios with global `Authorization` header set in `AuthContext`
- Design tokens via Tailwind `@layer components` in `theme.css`
- Every page follows "guardian-" class convention
- Protected routes via `<ProtectedRoute module="X">` HOC
- Navigation items filtered by privilege via `getVisibleNavItems(canRead, isAdmin)`

### AI Execution
- `cleanSchema()` sanitizes JSON schemas for Gemini compatibility
- `sanitizeResponse()` strips markdown code fences before JSON parsing
- `fileToGenerativePart()` converts uploaded files to Gemini multimodal parts
- Provider strategy pattern: `executeGoogleNative()` vs `executeOpenAICompatible()`

---

## 12. NPM Scripts

### Backend (`back/`)
| Script | Command | Purpose |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `npm run dev` | `nodemon src/server.js` | Development with auto-reload |
| `npm start` | `node src/server.js` | Production |
| `npm run seed` | `node src/seed.js` | Seed database with base data |
| `npm run build` | echo (no-op) | Required by Render |

### Frontend (`front/`)
| Script | Command | Purpose |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `npm run dev` | `vite` | Dev server on :5173 |
| `npm run build` | `vite build` | Production build |
| `npm run preview` | `vite preview` | Preview production build |
